webpackJsonp([0xa01b85c85d89],{855:function(t,e){t.exports={data:{wordpressPost:{title:"No We Can&#8217;t Hate Elsa Pataky &#8211; And Yes We Tried",content:'<p><strong>Actress Elsa Pataky</strong> has been named as the newest face of <strong>L&#8217;oreal Paris</strong> and well, you hardly need to ask why. The Spanish-born actress, model, wife and mother of three, is devastatingly beautiful. End of story.</p>\n<p>Annoyingly, she&#8217;s also delightful so you know, we can&#8217;t even dislike her. Not really.</p>\n<figure id="attachment_1744" style="width: 300px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1744" src="http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/19194521/fashion-jpg-300x260.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="260" srcset="http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/19194521/fashion-jpg-300x260.jpg 300w, http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/19194521/fashion-jpg.jpg 599w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /><figcaption class="wp-caption-text"><em><strong>Pretty, pretty, pretty and that hair? Gorgeous. Image: Instagram/@elsapatakyconfidential</strong></em></figcaption></figure>\n<p>The A-lister, who is married to Aussie boy <strong>Chris Hemsworth</strong> and divides her time between LA and Byron Bay, is the new face of <strong>Botanicals Fresh Care</strong> &#8211; the latest haircare release by L&#8217;Oreal Paris.</p>\n<p>“I love using this range of products – everything from the scent to how it makes my hair feel and the beautiful packaging”, says Elsa.</p>\n<figure id="attachment_1745" style="width: 300px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1745" src="http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/19194653/Loreal-jpg-300x192.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="192" srcset="http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/19194653/Loreal-jpg-300x192.jpg 300w, http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/19194653/Loreal-jpg-768x492.jpg 768w, http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/19194653/Loreal-jpg.jpg 922w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /><figcaption class="wp-caption-text"><strong><em>She attended a launch for the range in Sydney. Image: Instagram/@elsapatakyconfidential</em></strong></figcaption></figure>\n<p>But then she would right? At least, that&#8217;s what we thought when we read that statement. So we tried the range ourselves. And truth is, it&#8217;s excellent. It smells delicious, lathers beautifully and leaves hair light and bouncy. Those who tends towards frizz will need a smoothing oil or anti-fly-away serum afterwards but otherwise &#8211; this is a damn fine range.</p>\n<p>Launching in May, the range of products is made from natural botanical ingredients sourced from around the world. The formulations contain no parabens, silicone or colourants, and the ­­­eco-conscious packaging is recycled and recyclable after use.</p>\n<figure id="attachment_1746" style="width: 300px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1746" src="http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/19194711/Elsa-jpg-300x191.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="191" srcset="http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/19194711/Elsa-jpg-300x191.jpg 300w, http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/19194711/Elsa-jpg-768x489.jpg 768w, http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/19194711/Elsa-jpg.jpg 926w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /><figcaption class="wp-caption-text"><strong><em>Elsa announced her new role via social media. She has a LOT of followers. Image: Instagram/@elsapatakyconfiential</em></strong></figcaption></figure>\n<p>The range is made up of four pillars, each containing a shampoo, conditioner, mask and treatment. The ingredients are sustainably grown, extracted and concentrated by expert botanists, and created to target a different hair type:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Geranium</strong>, whose oil is distilled to provide lustre and restore vibrancy to dull or coloured hair</li>\n<li>Lipid-rich<strong> Safflower, </strong>to indulge and nourish dry hair</li>\n<li>Revalitising<strong> Coriander </strong>extracts, to invigorate the senses and strengthen fragile hair, and</li>\n<li>Extracted <strong>Camelina</strong> oil, to discipline and smooth unruly hair</li>\n</ul>\n<p>L’Oréal Paris Spokesmodels Doutzen Kroes, Karlie Kloss and Luma Grothe are the faces of the range globally.</p>\n<figure id="attachment_1747" style="width: 300px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img class="size-medium wp-image-1747" src="http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/19194917/e-jpg-300x192.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="192" srcset="http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/19194917/e-jpg-300x192.jpg 300w, http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/19194917/e-jpg-768x490.jpg 768w, http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/19194917/e-jpg.jpg 924w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /><figcaption class="wp-caption-text"><strong><em>She is irritatingly pretty &#8211; and also, genuinely sweet and clever too &#8211; even more annoying. Image: Instagram/@elsapatakyconfidential</em></strong></figcaption></figure>\n<p>“We are thrilled to have Elsa on board as the Botanicals ambassador to bring this beautiful new brand to Australia. She is natural, fresh, down to earth and perfectly embodies the Botanicals ethos”, says L’Oréal Paris Marketing Director, Lauren Crawley.</p>\n<p>Yup. We get that.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n',better_featured_image:{source_url:"http://dcqiwphk5imn5.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/19193129/Else-sun-jpg.jpg"},categories:[{slug:"hair",name:"Hair"}]},site:{siteMetadata:{title:"The Beauty Insider"}}},pathContext:{id:"5956b3f1-d7a2-5eb9-b98a-627d7b560e41"}}}});
